cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and summarization. The use of a neural model to predict sentence positions also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the task of summarization involves information retrieval and ranking, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of probability distributions and the mention of "strong features" suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
